How to stream GDS file into Cadence

1.  Stream GDS into an existing library

    CIW -> File -> Import -> Stream ...

    Input file: the gds file name
    Library Name: the existing library name
    Click Options on the top right, turn on "Skip Undefined Layer-Purpose Pair".
    OK on all forms.

    Stream in take some time. After it is done, a message will pop up.

2.  Stream GDS into a new library
   
    (1) Get an ASCII technology file.  You may use one of the following methods:

        -- link or copy /rds/prod/HOTCODE/techs/<tech>/cadence/default/<tech>.tf
        -- CIW->Technology->Dump, select a technology library (e.g. ch25a, bc35)
           Select All, enter a file name in ASCII technology file field.

    (2) CIW -> File -> Import -> Stream ...

        Input File: the gds file name
        Library Name: a library name you want to create
        ASCII Technology File Name: the file name created in (1)

3.  Stream GDS in with a special map file

    In the stream in form, click User-Defined Data, enter the map file as
    Layer Map Table.

    Layer map file template:

    #DFII Layer     DFII Layer      GDS Layer       GDS Layer
    #Name           Purpose         Number          Data Type
    nwell           drawing         1               0
    active          drawing         2               0

